    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <section class="mb-12">
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Subscription box businesses in Malaysia have exploded — from beauty and wellness boxes to curated snacks and hobby kits. What sets successful subscription brands apart? Branded, premium unboxing experiences that drive customer retention and social media buzz. Custom carton boxes are your most powerful marketing tool.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Why Subscription Boxes Need Custom Carton Packaging</h2>
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">The Unboxing Experience is Your Marketing</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">The moment a subscriber opens your box, they form an impression. A premium, branded carton creates a memorable experience worth sharing on Instagram, TikTok, and Facebook. This free marketing can increase retention by 20–30% and attract new subscribers through social proof.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Brand Recognition at Scale</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Recurring subscribers receive your box every month. Custom cartons with your logo, colors, and tagline reinforce brand identity with every delivery. This builds emotional connection and reduces churn across Balakong, KL, Selangor, and throughout Peninsular Malaysia.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Product Protection & Presentation</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Subscription contents are curated and valuable. Quality cartons with interior dividers and padding protect products during transit and enhance perceived value. Cheap packaging contradicts premium positioning.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">Designing Subscription Box Cartons: Key Considerations</h2>
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Size & Weight Optimization</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Subscription boxes must balance premium feel with shipping cost efficiency. Oversized boxes inflate postage; undersized boxes feel cheap. Work with Quinocycle to right-size your carton for your average product bundle. Consider different sizes for different months or seasons.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Branded Printing & Graphics</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Your carton's exterior should feature your logo, brand colors, tagline, and possibly customer testimonials or upcoming theme information. Full-color offset or digital printing makes boxes pop. Matte or glossy finishes can be specified based on your brand aesthetic.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Interior Design & Padding</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Don't forget the inside. Custom corrugated dividers, tissue paper, and filler keep products secure and add to the premium unboxing experience. Many subscription brands include personalized thank-you cards or seasonal messages inside the carton.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Easy-Open Features</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Subscribers shouldn't struggle to open your box. Integrated tear-tabs, perforated flaps, or foldable top closures make unboxing effortless. A smooth open experience increases positive sentiment and prevents negative reviews.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12 bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-8">
